descript.abstract: An polygon feature class of Miami-Dade County's Urban Development Boundary(UDB) and Urban Expansion Area (UEA). These boundaries were adopted by the Board of County Commissioners (BCC) as per recommendation.
descript.purpose: This layer was designed for the Comprehensive Development Master Plan amendment process, permitting of construction and assigning land use/ development capacity. It was also, designed for the LandUse Mapping Application (LUMA project). This layer is mainly used by the Department of Planning and Zoning (DP&Z) for mapping and analysis purposes.
descript.supplinf:
Procedures_Used: Appended the Urban Developement Boundary and the Urban Expansion Area. And grap the shoreline arcs from poutline since, it aligned better with Digital Map Library (DML) data, which is the landuse orignial state.
UDB and UEA was created by using ArcInfo to append tiles from the LandUse layer that are adjacent to the UDB into one coverage. Then, did a dissolve to determine the UDB line.
Revisions: Date: December 2011 By: Dany Martinez Reason: The layer has been updated to reflect UDB boundary only. Planning Department decided to temporaly remove UEA polygons from the layer until final boundary deliniation is concluded in Southern Miami Dade County.
Date: October 2011 By: Antoaneta Angelova Reason: The layer has been updated based on Ordinance 11-36 HOMESTEAD SPEEDWAY Adopted by the Board of County Commissioners on 7/7/2011 (File Number: 111342) and was subsequently found in compliance by State Land Planning Agency. The 2015 Urban Development Boundary (UDB) is: 1. Expanded to include an area of ±120 Acres between SW 132 and SW 142 Avenues, and between theoretical SW 333 and SW 336 Streets previously included in UEA. 2. Subtracted with ±120 acres south of the speedway generally bounded by SW 344 and SW 352 Streets and SW 137 and SW 132 Avenues. 2. Minor technical adjustment is made to the 2015 Urban Development Boundary (UDB) to match the boundaries of Homestead Air Force Base (folio #3070070000150). This added to the previous UDB boundary approximately 5 Acres Southwest of theoretical SW 300 St. and SW 112 Avenue.
Date: October 2009 By: Dany M. Martinez Machado Reason: The layer has been updated according to an Amendment to the CDMP adopted by the Board of County Commisioners (Ordinance No. 08-45 from Apr.24,2008 refered to Application No. 8, April 2007-08 Amendment cycle), as detected and become official after State of Florida Court ruling (No.SC06-2333) and DCA approval (Rule 9J-11.012) in July 2009. The Area was part of the UEA and was incorporated to the UDB (Area located on TRS 543931 and described as located on Southside of SW 88 th Street, west of SW 167 Ave.
Date: June 2008 By: Antoaneta Angelova Reason: The layer is updated with minor technical adjustment of the the boundary between UDB and UEA in TownshipRangeSection # 553906 between SW 90 St and WS 96 ST. The UDB line is extended West to SW 172 nd AVE to fallow the Property File layer.
Date: September 2007 By: Antoaneta Angelova Reason: The layer is updated to reflect an Amendment to the CDMP adopted by the Board of County Commisioners 2005-6 Cycle. Application #5 Ordinance 06-43 from April 19, 2006 and Ordinance # 06-116 from August 24, 2006. Extended the section of UDB between NW 97th AV and NW 154th ST West to Florida Turnpike. This area was part of UEA, now it is included in UDB.
Date: June 2006 By: Antoaneta Angelova Reason: Modifed layer as per Ordinance #05-219 from October 2005. To remove a section of UDB 2, bounded on the East by NW 147 Ave, on the North by the northern boundary of UDB 2, on the West by NW 157th Ave, and on the south by SW 8th Street.
Date: October2005 By: GIS Technical Support Staff Reason: The data was converted from the legacy coverage format to the ArcGIS Geodatabase feature class format.
Date: January 2003 By: J. Charles Reason: The Beacon Lakes Development of Regional Impact (DRI) application, requested an amendment to the CDMP LandUse Plan Map. Dade County code Sec 2-116.1(5)(a).
Reviews_Applied_to_Data: Data is reviewed by the DP&Z, GIS Data Administrator and GIS Metadata Administrator.
Other_References_Cited: Board of County Commissioners (BCC) adopted CDMP maps.
